Program: Crossing Continents
Title: Wrestling out of Poverty
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b05s3gz2
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 4 May 2015
In rural India, wrestling often attracts larger crowds than cricket. And for poor, farming communities in Maharashtra, a wrestler in the family can also mean a ticket out of poverty. For Crossing Continents, Rupa Jha meets the young fighters and their families, and explores how this ancient sport is breaking down caste barriers. Linda Pressly producing. Show less